h3. Summary

REST API update of an issue does not accept the *accountId* parameter. 


h3. Steps to Reproduce

Update a user field (ie Reporter) using REST API and use the AccounID parameter. 

{code}
curl --request PUT \
  --url 'https://<site>.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/issue/<ISSUE_KEY>' \
  -u email_address:apitoken \
  --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  --data '{
  "fields": {
    "reporter": {"accountId": "<ACCOUNT ID>"}
    }}'
{code}


h3. Expected Results

Since *accountId* parameter is used to specify the ID of a user when fetching data via REST API, the update method should accept it as well. 

h3. Actual Results

*accountId* is not accepted for updating an issue via REST API. 

{code}
{"errorMessages":[],"errors":{"reporter":"Reporter is required."}}
{code}

h3.Workaround

*id* is accepted instead of *accountId* when updating an issue via REST API. 

{code}
curl --request PUT \
  --url 'https://<site>.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/issue/<ISSUE_KEY>' \
  -u email_address:apitoken \
  --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  --data '{
  "fields": {
    "reporter": {"id": "<ACCOUNT ID>"}
    }}'
{code}

h3. Summary
When trying to create an epic via REST API v3, for example:
{code}
curl --request POST \
  --url 'https://<instance>..atlassian.net/rest/api/3/issue' \
  --header 'Authorization: Bearer <access_token>' \
  --header 'Accept: application/json' \
  --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  --data '{
{code}

It returns
{code}
{
"errorMessages": [],
"errors":

{ "customfield_10010": "Operation value must be an object" }
}
{code}

customfield_10010 is Epic Name. Upon checking the datatype for Epic Name, it seems to be String but it's still throwing out the error.

h3. Environment
* REST API v3

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create an EPIC via REST API v3

h3. Expected Results
Epic is created

h3. Actual Results
{code}
{
"errorMessages": [],
"errors":

{ "customfield_10010": "Operation value must be an object" }
}
{code}

h3.Workaround
Run in REST API v2. For example:
{code}
curl --request POST \
  --url 'https://<instance>..atlassian.net/rest/api/2/issue' \
  --header 'Authorization: Bearer <access_token>' \
  --header 'Accept: application/json' \
  --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  --data '{
{code}
